CatDescriptText: Miss Eleanor Kinkelpearl, student, Squirrel Hill was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, January 7, 1961, pg. A1 with question: "Admitting many factors cause juvenile delinquency, which one do you think is the major contributor to this increasing social illness?" answer reads: "I imagine it would be the family.  I suppose if there is a happy family, the child would feel secure and the parents would have no worries....And another cause, perhaps, is because some young groups make it social to be delinquent...."
